  "prompt": "How to get more RP (free) than 400 in LoL?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, there's no legitimate way to consistently get more than the occasional small amount of free RP in League of Legends. Riot Games' business model relies on players purchasing RP to buy cosmetics and other items. Getting large amounts of RP for free would undermine that model.\n\nHere's a breakdown of why it's difficult and what little options you have:\n\n*   **Riot's Stance:** Riot doesn't give away significant amounts of free RP regularly. This is to encourage players to support the game's development by purchasing RP.\n\n*   **No legitimate methods:** There are no legitimate ways to regularly earn a lot of free RP. Offers that promise this are almost always scams.\n\n*   **Riot Support (Small Amounts Only):** Riot Support is your best bet for *small* amounts of RP, usually less than 100. You can submit a ticket if you're a little short on RP to buy something. You can try to get a *small amount* of RP from them.\n\n    *   **How to do it:** Create a Support Ticket on the Riot Games website (not in the client). Explain your situation politely. Often, you'll need to submit a drawing, poem, or another creative piece related to League of Legends. They will then grant you the remaining RP needed to buy something (usually a skin).\n\n    *   **Important Considerations:**\n\n        *   Don't be greedy. Ask for a reasonable amount (usually under 50-100).\n        *   Be polite and respectful in your ticket.\n        *   This is a one-time (or very infrequent) thing. Don't try to do it often.\n\n**Here's what to avoid:**\n\n*   **Scams:** Be extremely wary of websites, videos, or programs that promise large amounts of free RP. These are almost always scams designed to steal your account information or install malware on your computer.\n*   **Account Sharing/Boosting:** Account sharing and boosting are against Riot's Terms of Service and can result in permanent account bans.\n*   **RP Generators:** These are scams. There is no legitimate RP generator. They are designed to steal your account information or install malware.\n*   **Surveys/Offers:** While some legitimate survey sites exist, offers for free RP are usually scams or lead to very small rewards that aren't worth the effort.\n\n**In Summary:**\n\nThe only reliable way to get RP is to purchase it. Be careful of anything promising otherwise. Riot occasionally holds events or promotions that might offer small amounts of RP, but these are infrequent. While you can contact Riot Support for a small amount of RP in special circumstances, don't rely on it as a regular method. Protect your account by avoiding scams and following Riot's Terms of Service.",
